{
  "stem": "15962.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was a very special [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] surgeon, held in high esteem and took a liking to me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I was in this hospital about six weeks, very slowly regaining life while the others were mostly in another barrack on the base, kind of living as scavengers.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were just thousands of tons of material brought in daily by huge American transport planes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Americans had everything they-- the second day of setting up camp, they had hot showers and whenever they want a bar of chocolate or a cigarette, they would open with a bayonet K-rations or whatever they were called and just take out what they want and threw the rest away.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This was in direct contrast to the Russian army that we encountered a few weeks later.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The Americans were very kind and very friendly, and the other boys who were-- some of them were also hospitalized, but most of them were simply just slowly getting back their way toward improving the situation.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] At that time there was great confusion in Europe.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And getting back home was no easy task, because there was no transport.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Trains were not running.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Bridges were down.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "At one point, there was a [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] car from Czechoslovakia that came.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it turned out it was father of one of us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He was a physician who survived Auschwitz and by some way found out where his son was and came to take, take him home.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That was our kind of first direct contact with our home country.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
